  "prompt": "Technical product manager questions?",
  "response": "Here are some common technical product manager (TPM) interview questions:\n\nTechnical Knowledge:\n1. Describe your technical background\n2. How do you assess technical feasibility of a product?\n3. What programming languages do you know?\n4. How do you work with engineering teams?\n\nProduct Strategy:\n1. How would you prioritize product features?\n2. Describe a product roadmap you've developed\n3. How do you validate product ideas?\n4. What metrics do you use to measure product success?\n\nProblem-Solving:\n1. Explain a complex technical problem you solved\n2. How would you handle disagreements with engineers?\n3. Walk through your product development process\n4. Describe a challenging product launch\n\nScenario-Based Questions:\n1. How would you improve [specific product]?\n2. Design a new feature for [existing product]\n3. Handle a product with declining user engagement\n4. Manage competing stakeholder requirements\n\nTechnical Deep Dives:\n1. Explain system architecture concepts\n2. Discuss scalability and performance considerations\n3. Understand API design principles\n4. Describe cloud infrastructure fundamentals\n\nLeadership:\n1. How do you motivate cross-functional teams?\n2. Describe your communication style\n3. Handle conflicts in product development\n4. Balance technical and business requirements\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these areas?",
